<p>The <a href="https://www.apaonline.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">American Philosophical Association</a> (APA) has announced that it has established two new prizes for papers in two sets of philosophical areas.<span id="more-54251"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-54252 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/apa-prize-ribbons.png" alt="" width="524" height="350" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/apa-prize-ribbons.png 975w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/apa-prize-ribbons-300x200.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/apa-prize-ribbons-768x513.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/apa-prize-ribbons-400x267.png 400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 524px) 100vw, 524px" /></p>
<p>The prizes are named in honor of Milton K. Munitz and Lenore Bloom Munitz, and will be awarded to papers chosen from among those submitted to the Eastern Division Meetings of the APA.</p>
<p>They are the <em>Milton K. Munitz Prize in Metaphysics, Ontology, and Cosmology</em> and the <em>Lenore Bloom Munitz Prize in Value Theory, Social Philosophy, and Civic Virtue</em>.</p>
<p>The prizes areÂ $1,000 each, and will be awarded at the Eastern Division meeting for which the winning papers are accepted.</p>
<p>You can learn more about Milton K. Munitz <a href="https://www.miltonkmunitzsociety.org/about-milton-k-munitz/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
